6 Subject: Regulated drugs; psilocybin; therapeutic use
7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to decriminalize
8 the possession, cultivation, and noncommercial personal use of psilocybin-
9 containing mushrooms by adults 21 years of age and older and establishes the
10 Psilocybin Therapeutic Consultation Program. The Program is tasked with
11 developing an education, training, and consultation model for the safe use of
12 psilocybin-containing mushrooms designed and overseen by health providers.
13 Health providers eligible for licensure include licensed mental health
14 professionals, physicians, nurse practitioners, and other qualified healthcare
15 practitioners as determined by the Program. Providers must complete a
16 certified training program focused on psilocybin use, safety protocols, and
17 integration practices. Licensed providers may offer initial health evaluations to
18 determine the suitability of psilocybin use, guided psilocybin sessions in a
19 safe, controlled environment and protected by State law, and post-session
20 integration support to maximize therapeutic outcomes.
